@node Oprogramu "Introduction"

    This program can do only one thing. You can enter some polygon (check
examples), then You can enter one point and @{FG Shine}Blue Polygon@{FG text} says you if
the point is in or out of the polygon.

    This program comes with the algorithm of evaluate (in @{I}PCQ Pascal@{UI}).

    This program is a new standart of GUI of system programs of @{B}Blue Legend@{UB}.
@endnode

@node Freeware
    This program is freeware. You can copy it as You wish, but the content
of the archive have to be unchanged.

    The author @{B}can not@{UB} be made responsible for any damage which is caused
by using this program.
@endnode

@node Pozadavky "Requirements"
    @{"Blue Polygon" link Oprogramu} needs

 - min. OS 3.0

 - reqtools.library version 38 or greater (included)

 - about 150 kB if free memory

Recommended:

 - Harddisk

 - Installer for instalation

 - BluePolygon.catalog (localization)

@endnode

@node Instalace "Instalation"

Please, use the installation utility. :)

Or copy the content of archive to some directory on harddisk.
In the directory icons you can find alternative icons for the @{B}4-colors
standart@{UB} and @{B}New Icons@{UB}
@endnode

@node Program "Usage"

    @{"Blue Polygon" link Oprogramu} uses a bubbles like hints.

@{B}Buttons:@{UB}
    --------------- ----------
    |New|Load|Save| |Edit|Ask|
    --------------- ----------

@{B}New@{UB}     - CleanUp the current polygon

@{B}Load@{UB}    - Open some polygon from disk

@{B}Save@{UB}    - Save current project to disk


@{B}Edit@{UB}    - Here you can edit polygon

            You can add or remove points using gadgets.
            You can change point's values using string gadget
            You can see a list of points

@{B}Ask@{UB}     - In two string gadgets you can enter the coordinations of point.
          If You click on the gadget Evaluate You get the result

@{I}
I'm sorry for this very simple documentation, but I'm too lazy to write
some other :-|
@{UI}
@endnode

@node algo "Algorithm"

    You can find the algorithm in the directory @{B}Algo@{UB} file @{"PolEval.i" link "algo/poleval.i/MAIN"}

    Remember, this is a part of source in @{I}PCQ Pascal@{UI}.

    @{I}I'm sorry for Czech names of functions and variable (sometimes) @{UI}
@endnode

